{"id": 225028496, "title": "Scarlett Johansson Takes the AI Fight to Big Tech, and Big Media Should Follow | Commentary", "text": "Does anyone really believe OpenAI CEO Sam Altman anymore? Altman launched OpenAI in 2015 with a mission to develop AI that \u201cbenefits all of humanity.\u201d Fast forward nine years later, humanity be damned \u2014 Altman and his ego needed a \u201cHer\u201d moment when OpenAI launched its latest version, ChatGPT-4o. Problem is, Scarlett Johansson was having none of it. Neither is much of the creative community, which is finally beginning to understand its collective power and is rising up to say, \u201cStop the madness!\u201d That \u201cmadness\u201d is the arrogant taking of not just creative works \u2014 which is the subject of an ever-growing number of infringement cases in the courts \u2013 but now also the taking of creators\u2019 personas themselves.", "summary": "<p>The creative community has had enough with Sam Altman and Silicon Valley\u2019s \u201ctake first, apologize later\u201d strategy</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.thewrap.com/scarlett-johansson-ai-fight-explained-sam-altman/\">Scarlett Johansson Takes the AI Fight to Big Tech, and Big Media Should Follow | Commentary</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.thewrap.com\">TheWrap</a>.</p>", "url": "https://www.thewrap.com/scarlett-johansson-ai-fight-explained-sam-altman/", "image": "https://i0.wp.com/www.thewrap.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/scarlett-johansson-sam-altman.jpg?fit=1200%2C675&ssl=1", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 13:15:00", "author": "Peter Csathy", "authors": ["Peter Csathy"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": -0.061}